\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 34. A. laevissima} Klokov in Schischkin,{\i  Fl. URSS}{\b  23}: 708 (1958). Like {\b 33} but mostly glabrous (rarely more or less rough at base); middle internodes 1½-2 times as long as the leaves; leaves 10-40 × 0·5-1 mm, linear to acicular, glabrous, the margin more or less weakly revolute; pedicels not more than 1·5 mm; corolla 3-6 mm, the tube 1½-2 times as long as lobes, the lobes obscurely appendiculate; fruit (2·5-)3-4·5 mm, with more or less obtuse tubercles. •{\i  S.E. Russia, westwards to} 40° 30' {\i E. }Rs (C, E).
\par 

\par 

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 35. A. graveolens} Bieb. ex Schultes & Schultes fil., {\i Mantissa}{\b  3}: 376 (1827). Shoots green. Stems 10-35 cm, geniculate-ascending, more or less weak, rough at the base, usually with conspicuous, short, non-flowering shoots at the nodes; middle internodes 1-3 times as long as the leaves. Leaves (15-)25-30(-40) × 0·4-1·2 mm, linear to acicular, acute, patent and falcate to recurved, usually shortly hairy; margin distinctly revolute. Bracts narrowly lanceolate, glabrous or ciliate, scarcely exceeding the fruits; pedicels 0-1·5(-3) mm. Corolla 3·5-4 mm, broadly hypocrateriform to narrowly infundibuliform; tube 1-1½ times as long as lobes; lobes distinctly appendiculate. Fruit (2-)3-4 mm, densely covered with squamiform tubercles. •{\i  E. Ukraine and S. Russia, from the Dnepr to E. of the Don.} Rs (C, W, E).
\par 

\par 

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 36. A. diminuta} Klokov in Schischkin, {\i Fl. URSS}{\b  23}: 707 (1958). Like {\b 35} but shoots glaucous; stems 15-35 cm, usually glabrous and smooth throughout; leaves 6-20(-25) × 0·5-1·2 mm; pedicels not more than 1 mm; corolla 3·5-4·5 mm, the tube equalling the lobes; fruit with acute tubercles.{\i  N.W. coast of Caspian Sea.} Rs (E).
\par 

\par 

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 37. A. leiograveolens} M. Popov & Chrshan.,{\i  Bull. Soc. Nat. Moscou} nov. ser.,{\b  50}({\b 5-6}): 96 (1945). Like {\b 35} but leaves 10-25 × 0·3-0·7 mm, glabrous; bracts glabrous; fruit 2-3 mm, almost without or with only a few, scattered squamiform tubercles. •{\i  C. Ukraine} ({\i along the middle course of the Dnepr}). Rs (W).
\par 

