\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 40. A. littoralis} Sibth. & Sm.,{\i  Fl. Graec. Prodr.}{\b  1}: 89 (1806). Like {\b 39} but stems 10-55 cm, procumbent and rooting at the base, almost always shortly hispid throughout; flowering stems usually with more than 25 internodes, which are 1-2 times as long as the leaves; leaves 3-10(-14) × 0·6-1·4 mm, more or less appressed, the margin weakly revolute; corolla 2-4 mm; fruit densely covered with short setae.{\i  Maritime sands. N. coast of Turkey-in-Europe. }Tu. ({\i N. Anatolia.})
