\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 41. A. incana} Sibth. & Sm.,{\i  Fl. Graec. Prodr.}{\b  1}: 88 (1806). Stems (7-)10-40(-45) cm, more or less woody at base, ascending, rigid, robust, more or less branched, more or less hairy; internodes usually more than 12, the upper distinctly longer. Leaves (3-)8-15(-20) × (0·5-)0·8-1·2 mm, linear, more or less acute, densely hairy, sometimes glabrescent, the margin distinctly revolute. Inflorescences with sessile to long-pedunculate capitula. Corolla hypocrateriform, reddish, shortly hairy, sometimes glabrescent; tube (4·5-)5-6·5(-8) mm; lobes 2-3 mm, ovate, acuminate and more or less patent. Fruit c. 1·5 mm, shortly hairy. 2n = 44. {\i Stony places from the coast to the montane zone. • Kriti.} Cr.
