\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 44. A. hirsuta} Desf.,{\i  Fl. Atl.}{\b  1}: 127 (1798). Stems (10-)15-50 (-60) cm, erect, rigid, robust, branched, hairy below or often subglabrous; internodes usually more than 12, the upper distinctly longer. Leaves (10-)12-20 × (0·5-)0·8-1(-1·2) mm, lanceolate to linear, long-acuminate, thin, more or less hairy beneath, mostly subglabrous above, green when dry. Inflorescences usually with several long-pedunculate capitula. Corolla hypocrateriform, brownish-red to pale pink, shortly hairy or glabrous; tube 5-7(-9) mm; lobes 2-3(-4) mm, ovate, flat. Fruit (2-)3-4 mm, glabrous. 2n = 22, 44. {\i Stony places and roadsides}
